Path: godot/classes/class_audiostreamwav.rst
Summary: The AudioStreamWAV class is a resource for loading and playing WAV audio files in Godot.

AudioStreamWAV
A resource for loading and playing WAV audio files.

Inherits: AudioStream < Resource < Object

Description:
This resource is used to load and play WAV audio files. It supports various WAV formats, including PCM, ADPCM, and others. The audio data is loaded into memory, making it suitable for short sound effects or music that needs to be accessed quickly. For longer audio files or streaming, consider using AudioStreamOggVorbis or AudioStreamMP3.

Properties:
data (PackedByteArray): The raw audio data.
format (int): The audio format. See AudioStreamWAV.Format constants.
mix_rate (int): The mix rate (frequency) of the audio in Hz.
loop (bool): Whether the audio should loop.
loop_offset (int): The offset in samples where the loop should start.
seek_position (int): The position in samples to seek to when the audio is played.

Methods:
load_from_buffer(buffer: PackedByteArray, format: int, channels: int, mix_rate: int) → bool
Loads audio data from a buffer.

save_to_wav(path: String) → bool
Saves the audio data to a WAV file.

Enums:
Format
FormatPCM8 (0): 8-bit PCM audio.
FormatPCM16 (1): 16-bit PCM audio.
FormatIMAADPCM (2): IMA ADPCM audio.
FormatMP3 (3): MP3 audio (not directly supported by this class, usually handled by other stream types).
FormatVorbis (4): Vorbis audio (not directly supported by this class, usually handled by other stream types).
FormatUncompressed (5): Uncompressed audio (generic).
FormatPCM24 (6): 24-bit PCM audio.
FormatPCM32 (7): 32-bit PCM audio.
FormatG711A (8): G711 A-law audio.
FormatG711U (9): G711 µ-law audio.
FormatVorbis_Legacy (10): Legacy Vorbis format.
FormatADPCM (11): Generic ADPCM audio.
FormatDSD (12): DSD audio.
FormatMax (13): Maximum value for format.
